7. Feature Logic Summary

7.1 Quiz and Score Generation
Users complete a 25-question quiz covering Diet, Medication, Symptoms, and Lifestyle. The answers are sent to the backend through /api/assess and are also interpreted on the frontend for immediate dashboard rendering.

7.2 Your Health Status
This section converts the user result into:
- overall gut health score
- category-wise bar graph
- trend line graph
- issue detection cards
- friendly dialogue box

7.3 Smart Tools
This section explains the user pattern in simplified terms:
- Health Pattern Analyzer
- Habit Path Guide
- confidence-style visual indicator
- top influences on gut health

7.4 Future Outlook
This section predicts what may happen if current habits continue:
- projection line graph
- short text explanation
- high-impact focus areas

7.5 Gut Balance
This section shows a simplified ecosystem view using:
- diversity trend
- category support bars
- friendly commentary
- helpful actions

7.6 Gut Archetype
This section maps the user to one of four practical profiles:
- Balanced Gut
- Sensitive Gut
- Inflamed Gut
- Slow Digestion Type

Each archetype includes:
- simple description
- likely traits
- next best actions

7.7 Food Log + Next-Day Analysis
The food log allows users to record meals and see whether a food appears gut-friendly, neutral, or triggering. The page also summarizes yesterday's meals, estimates their likely effect on today's gut comfort, and suggests a better next-day plan.

7.8 Check-in
The check-in page captures daily signals like bloating, cramps, nausea, gas, heartburn, water, mood, sleep, and stress for ongoing monitoring.

7.9 Profile + BMI
The Profile screen includes:
- user identity summary
- category performance cards
- BMI calculator
- BMI category
- BMI trend graph
- retake assessment action

