12. User Manual

12.1 Login / Register
Users can create an account using name, email, and password, or sign in with existing credentials. Guest-style flow is also supported through the dashboard routing logic once a user enters the app flow.

12.2 Quiz
The quiz presents 25 questions one by one. Each answer updates the user profile and contributes to diet, medication, symptom, and lifestyle scoring.

12.3 Home Screen
After finishing the quiz, the user lands on the Home screen. This screen shows the main result, powered-by message, category tiles, and shortcuts to deeper analysis sections.

12.4 Category Pages
Diet and Lifestyle cards are clickable and open focused pages with graphs, issue detection, and simple explanations. Symptoms and Medication also have focused summaries.

12.5 Analysis Screen
The Analysis tab provides a structured hub for:
- Your Health Status
- Smart Tools
- Future Outlook
- Gut Balance
- Gut Archetype

12.6 Check-in
Users can log how they feel on a given day to create lightweight day-to-day tracking.

12.7 Food Log
Users can add meals and review how yesterday's meals may be influencing today's digestion and comfort.

12.8 Profile
Users can view their personal details, result tier, category summaries, BMI status, BMI trend, and retake the assessment.

13. Dataset
The live user-facing experience primarily works from questionnaire responses and rule-based interpretation. The experimental model file backend/model.py generates synthetic data for XGBoost and KMeans experiments. This means the current academic project includes both:
- production-style app logic driven by questionnaire input
- prototype ML experimentation for future integration

